31/10/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Over 90 per cent of Macedonia's citizens want to see their country join the EU, according to the results of a survey conducted by the Institute for Sociological and Political-Legal Studies during the past week. The survey also found that while 56.3 per cent of the participants believe Macedonia is largely meeting the conditions for EU accession, 40.2 per cent are dissatisfied with the government's commitment to the process.
In other news, a donor conference held in New York on Friday resulted in pledges of $12m to fight unemployment in Macedonia. The UNDP sponsored the conference. (Macedonian Government Web site - 31/10/05; Utrinski Vesnik - 29/10/05; A1 TV - 28/10/05) 
